## Offline Flag Testing Complete âœ…

I've completed comprehensive testing of the HTTPie `--offline` flag feature. Here are the key findings:

### Test Summary
- **Total Tests:** 14
- **Passed:** 12
- **Failed:** 2

### Core Functionality (Working)
The `--offline` flag correctly:
- Builds and prints HTTP requests without sending them
- Handles GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE requests
- Supports authentication (Basic Auth and Bearer tokens)
- Processes URL query parameters (with `==` syntax)
- Handles JSON data fields (with `:=` syntax)
- Works with piped JSON input
- Respects output control flags (`--quiet`, `--verbose`, `--stream`)
- Works with the `--print` flag for selective output

### Identified Issues

**Critical Issue:** Method inference crashes when mixing data types without an explicit method
- Command: `http --offline https://httpbin.org/post --ignore-stdin name=value age:=25`
- Error: `AssertionError` in `_guess_method()`
- Workaround: Always explicitly specify the HTTP method

**UX Issue:** Headers must come after URL
- Incorrect: `http --offline X-Custom-Header:test-value GET https://api.example.com`
- Correct: `http --offline GET https://api.example.com X-Custom-Header:test-value`

### Comparison Note
The alternative tool `spie` (SwiftPie) does not have an offline flag equivalent.

